The paper deals with computational complexity and parameterized complexity of committee selection problem for approval-based voting rules, which falls under the category of computational game theory (cs.GT). The use of natural parameters and the study of approximation algorithms suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
